  "title": "Investment Banking Analyst (up to 12 months contract)",
  "description": "<p>Job Description <br />1) Assist the department in the execution of corporate finance transactions such as IPOs, M&A, Debt Advisory covering Leveraged/ Structured Financing, and other financial advisory engagements.</p><p>2) Conduct in-depth financial analysis, valuation and modeling to support transaction execution.</p><p>3) Preparing pitch materials for department's new business development activities, including materials such as pitchbooks and client presentations among others.</p><p>4) Responsible for coordinating the various project workstreams among internal and external stakeholders.</p><p>5) Assist in deal execution, including due diligence, financial modelling, and transaction structuring.</p><p>6) Assists the department on the day-to-day project management and cross-functional collaboration.<br /></p><p>Job Requirements<br />1) More than 1 year of experience in Investment Banking, Corporate Finance, Strategic Advisory, or related field</p><p>2) Outstanding analytical, communication, and interpersonal skills</p><p>3) Proficiency in Microsoft Excel, PowerPoint, and financial databases (i.e. Bloomberg, Capital IQ, etc.)</p><p>4) Client-ready data visualization skill and detailed-oriented</p><p>5) Ability to work effectively and perform in a fast-paced environment with tight deadlines.</p>",
